==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Razee
<hw>Ra*zee"</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*z⟦emac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
vaisseau <ets>ras⟦eacute⟧</ets>, fr. <ets>raser</ets> to raze, to cut
down ships. See <er>Raze</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, <er>Rase</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>An armed ship having her upper
deck cut away, and thus reduced to the next inferior rate, as a
seventy-four cut down to a frigate.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Razee</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Razee
<hw>Ra*zee"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Razeed</conjf> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*z⟦emac⟧d")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Razeeing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To cut down to a less
number of decks, and thus to an inferior rate or class, as a ship;
hence, to prune or abridge by cutting off or retrenching parts; <as>as,
to <ex>razee</ex> a book, or an article</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Razor</ent>⟦br⟧
